@Google pushed a new version of their oauthclient package [yesterday](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/oauth2client/2.0.0), moving it from 1.5.2 to 2.0. This change is backwards incompatible with even [their own example code](https://developers.google.com/api-client-library/python/auth/service-accounts).

I've added oauthclient in requirements.txt (since it was being pulled in transitively from the other google dependencies, but was directly used in Airflow code). I've also updated setup.py to peg the version < 2.0.0, which fixes the incompatibility.

Lastly, I added httplib2 directly to the requirements.txt since, again, it's being directly used in code, but didn't have a direct dependency defined.

Alright, I gave it a shot as I know this issue will hit Airbnb soon (we had this issue in the past, but we extended our mileage with cranking up the number of sessions in MySql and reducing the pool sizes)
